\cf0 Order of events:\
	- The number of players is determined. Each player will get 9 cards, so in a deck of 52 cards (jokers excluded), a single deck is used when there are less than 5 players (see later section for more details). \
	- Decks of cards are shuffled.\
	- Each player is dealt a hand consisting of the following: 3 known cards (in-hand), 3 unknown cards (face down)(off-hand), and 3 known cards (face up)(off-hand)\
	- A random person is selected to go first.\
	- The player is allowed to play any card onto the discard pile. They must replenish their hand to at least 3 cards.\
	- Play continues in a clockwise fashion.\
	- The next player is allowed to play any legal move (see later section), which generally means playing a card of equal rank or higher onto the discard pile. The player also then replenishes their hand to 3 cards from the pick-up pile.\
	- Play continues in this fashion until a player plays an illegal move, or cannot play a valid card, resulting in them picking up the discard pile and adding it to their in-hand.\
	- If a player has 3 or more cards in their in-hand, they do not need to replenish. \
	- Once all the cards in the player\'92s in-hand are played, and the replenish deck is empty, the player then starts playing from their off-hand. The same rules and general play continues as before, until the player\'92s known off-hand cards are out. Only then does the player start to play the unknown off-hand cards. If these are all played, that player is considered out of contention for being the loser (or considered the winner in some variations of the game).\
	- The remaining players continue to play unit all but one is eliminated. This person is considered the loser.\
